1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
fMRI doesn't watch thoughts — it tracks blood-oxygen changes linked to brain activity.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:07,600
This is called the BOLD signal.

3
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:10,000
But what does BOLD really mean?

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,800
When neurons fire, they need more oxygen...

5
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:15,600
and that’s where the blood comes in.

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:19,200
Researchers measure these changes, but interpreting them isn’t straightforward.

7
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:24,400
That’s why reverse inference can be misleading; it’s not always what it seems.

8
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:29,200
Imagine thinking you know what someone is feeling just by their scan...

9
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:31,200
but it’s far more complex.

10
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,600
Want to dive deeper into neuroscience?

11
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,000
Hit that subscribe button for more!
